### User:
what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com

### Response:


The command "ssh -i '~/UserKey.pem'" creates an SSH client that interacts with the server. It is used to establish a secure connection between two servers, and it can be used for remote access to other computers on the network.
